innocence
guiltlessness &c. adj.
incorruption, impeccability. clean hands, clear conscience, mens sibi conscia recti [Lat.] [Vergil]. innocent, lamb, dove. V. be innocent &c. adj.
nil conscire sibi nulla pallescere culpa [Lat.] [Horace]. acquit &c.
exculpate &c. (vindicate). Adj. innocent, not guilty
unguilty
guiltless, faultless, sinless, stainless, bloodless, spotless
clear, immaculate
rectus in curia [Lat.]
unspotted, unblemished, unerring
undefiled &c.
unhardened, Saturnian
Arcadian &c. (artless). inculpable, unculpable
unblamed, unblamable
blameless, unfallen, inerrable, above suspicion
irreproachable, irreprovable, irreprehensible
unexceptionable, unobjectionable, unimpeachable
salvable
venial &c.. harmless
inoffensive, innoxious, innocuous
dove-like, lamb-like
pure, harmless as doves
innocent as a lamb, innocent as the babe unborn
unreproved, unimpeached, unreproached. Adv. innocently &c. adj.
with clean hands
with a clear conscience, with a safe conscience. murus aeneus conscientia sana [Horace].
